{"title_page": "2020 Florida State Seminoles football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 2020\n| team = Florida State Seminoles  \n| image = Florida State Seminoles alternate logo.svg\n| image_size = 100\n| conference = Atlantic Coast Conference\n| division = Atlantic Division\n| short_conf = ACC\n| CoachRank = \n| APRank = \n| CFPRank =\n| record = 0\u20130\n| conf_record = 0\u20130\n| head_coach= [[Mike Norvell]]\n| hc_year = 1st\n| off_coach = Kenny Dillingham\n| oc_year = 1st\n| off_scheme = \n| def_coach = [[Adam Fuller]]\n| dc_year = 1st\n| def_scheme = \n| captain= \n| stadium = [[Doak Campbell Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 79,560)\n}}\n{{2020 ACC football standings}}\nThe '''2020 Florida State Seminoles football team''' will represent [[Florida State University]] during the [[2020 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Seminoles will play their home games at [[Doak Campbell Stadium]] in [[Tallahassee, Florida]], and compete as members of the Atlantic Division in the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]]. They will be lead by head coach [[Mike Norvell]], in his first season.\n\n==Previous season==\nFlorida State finished the [[2019 Florida State Seminoles football team|2019 season]] 6\u20137, 4\u20134 in ACC play, to finish in fourth place in the Atlantic Division. The Seminoles appeared in the [[2019 Sun Bowl|Sun Bowl]], losing to [[2019 Arizona State Sun Devils football team|Arizona State]], to complete consecutive losing seasons for the first time since the [[1975 Florida State Seminoles football team|1975]] and [[1976 Florida State Seminoles football team|1976]] seasons. [[Willie Taggart]] was fired prior to the end of the season and [[Odell Haggins]] served as interim coach for the remaining games.\n\n==Coaching staff==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Florida State Seminoles|color=white}}; text-ali