{"title_page": "Dushyant Ojha", "text_new": "'''Dushyant Ojha''' (December 1931\u2013April 14, 2020) was a [[journalist]] and Indian politician from [[Jaipur]], [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://zeenews.india.com/home/cpi-cpi-m-and-jd-s-join-hands-in-rajasthan_515022.html|title=CPI, CPI (M) and JD (S) join hands in Rajasthan|date=15 March 2009|work=Zee News|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He was ex-[[State Secretary]] of the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oneindia.com/2006/11/10/cpi-alleges-home-minister-responsible-for-stalemate-in-talks-1163151621.html|title=CPI alleges Home minister responsible for stalemate in talks|date=10 November 2006|work=OneIndia|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He was an active member of the party since 1953 till his death. He died on 14 April 2020 due to prolonged illness at [[CK Birla Hospital]] in Jaipur, Rajasthan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/bikaner/news/rajasthan-news-dushyant-ojha-of-cpi-passed-away-071649-7031586.html|title=\u0938\u0940\u092a\u0940\u0906\u0908 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0941\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0902\u0924 \u0913\u091d\u093e \u0915\u093e \u0928\u093f\u0927\u0928|date=15 April 2020|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ojha, Dushyant}}\n[[Category:Indian men]]\n[[Category:Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:1931 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n", "text_old": "'''Dushyant Ojha''' (December 1931\u2013April 14, 2020) was a [[journalist]] and Indian politician from [[Jaipur]], [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://zeenews.india.com/home/cpi-cpi-m-and-jd-s-join-hands-in-rajasthan_515022.html|title=CPI, CPI (M) and JD (S) join hands in Rajasthan|date=15 March 2009|work=Zee News|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He was ex-[[State Secretary]] of the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.oneindia.com/2006/11/10/cpi-alleges-home-minister-responsible-for-stalemate-in-talks-1163151621.html|title=CPI alleges Home minister responsible for stalemate in talks|date=10 November 2006|work=OneIndia|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> He was an active member of the party since 1953 till his death. He died on 14 April 2020 due to prolonged illness at [[CK Birla Hospital]] in Jaipur, Rajasthan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/bikaner/news/rajasthan-news-dushyant-ojha-of-cpi-passed-away-071649-7031586.html|title=\u0938\u0940\u092a\u0940\u0906\u0908 \u0915\u0947 \u0926\u0941\u0937\u094d\u092f\u0902\u0924 \u0913\u091d\u093e \u0915\u093e \u0928\u093f\u0927\u0928|date=15 April 2020|work=Dainik Bhaskar|access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ojha, Dushyant}}\n[[Category:Indian men]]\n[[Category:Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:1931 births]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dushyant_Ojha"}
{"title_page": "List of films based on video games", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\nThis page is a '''list of [[video game film|film adaptations of video games]]'''. These include local, international, direct-to-video and TV releases, and (in certain cases) online releases. They include their scores on [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the region in which they were released (for foreign adaptations), approximate budget, their approximate box office revenue (for theatrical releases), distributor of the film, and the publisher of the original game at the time the film was made (this means that publishers may change between two adaptations of the same game or game series, such as ''[[Mortal Kombat]]''). Also included are short films, cutscene films (made up of cutscenes and cinematics from the actual games), documentaries with video games as their subjects and films in which video games play a large part (such as ''[[Tron]]'' or ''[[WarGames]]'').\n\nFilms based on video games have often received negative reviews. Rotten Tomatoes's 2019 list titled ''Video Game Movies Ranked Worst to Best'' included only 3 films that received a fresh Tomatometer rating.{{efn|name=RTRanking|Rotten Tomatoes only included theatrically-released films with Tomatometer scores based on more than 20 reviews.}}<ref name= VideoGameRottenTomatoes>{{cite web |title=43 VIDEO GAME MOVIES RANKED WORST TO BEST |url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/video-game-movies-ranked-worst-to-best/ |accessdate=August 20, 2019 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes}}</ref>\n\n==Theatrical releases==\n\n===Hollywood (live-action)===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! Title !! Release date !! Worldwide box office !![[Rotten Tomatoes]] !! [[Metacritic]] \n!Distributor!! Original game publisher\n|-\n| ''[[Super Mario Bros. (film)|Super Mario Bros.]]'' || {{dts|1993|5|28}} || $20,915,465<ref>{{cite web